GERMAN ENGINEERING,

513
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:30,221
BEAUTIFUL WOMEN.

514
00:26:30,221 --> 00:26:32,624
YEAH, SURE. WHAT EVERY
RED-BLOODED AMERICAN WANTS.

515
00:26:32,624 --> 00:26:34,259
I ALREADY GOT
THE WOMAN PART.

516
00:26:34,259 --> 00:26:35,393
YOU DO?

517
00:26:35,393 --> 00:26:37,262
YEAH.

518
00:26:37,262 --> 00:26:40,098
LET ME SHOW YOU SOMETHING.

519
00:26:40,098 --> 00:26:43,134
IT'S MY LITTLE HONEY.

520
00:26:43,134 --> 00:26:45,937
THAT'S SHARON.
ISN'T SHE BEAUTIFUL?

521
00:26:45,937 --> 00:26:47,005
SHE'S NICE.

522
00:26:47,005 --> 00:26:49,407
NICE?
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL, MAN.

523
00:26:49,407 --> 00:26:53,011
BESIDES, THERE'S MORE
TO A PERSON THAN LOOKS.

524
00:26:53,011 --> 00:26:55,547
THERE'S TRUST,
THERE'S LOVE,

525
00:26:55,547 --> 00:26:57,182
THERE'S COMMITMENT.

526
00:26:57,182 --> 00:26:59,150
YOU GOT A POINT, JON.

527
00:27:02,954 --> 00:27:04,756
BUT...

528
00:27:04,756 --> 00:27:07,058
WHAT WOULD YOU DO
WITH HER?

529
00:27:07,058 --> 00:27:09,127
THE BLONDE IN THE BLACK.

530
00:27:10,328 --> 00:27:12,030
COME ON, KARLIN.

531
00:27:12,030 --> 00:27:16,201
LET'S SAY THAT SHARON
WOULD NEVER FIND OUT.

532
00:27:16,201 --> 00:27:17,802
WHAT'S THE POINT?

533
00:27:17,802 --> 00:27:20,538
I KNOW YOU GET
THE URGE, JON.

534
00:27:20,538 --> 00:27:23,975
