I CAN COUNT ON YOU.

564
00:28:52,230 --> 00:28:54,532
CAN I COUNT ON YOU, JON?

565
00:28:57,035 --> 00:29:00,371
YEAH. ABSOLUTELY.

566
00:29:01,539 --> 00:29:03,808
GOOD.

567
00:29:03,808 --> 00:29:06,377
ONE MORE.

568
00:29:06,377 --> 00:29:08,847
HEY, WHEN ARE WE
GOING TO GET

569
00:29:08,847 --> 00:29:11,116
TO GO ON THE AIR
WITH YOU?

570
00:29:11,116 --> 00:29:14,552
DENISE. CYNTHIA.
SO NICE TO SEE YOU LADIES.

571
00:29:14,552 --> 00:29:16,588
IF I DIDN'T KNOW
ANY BETTER,

572
00:29:16,588 --> 00:29:19,991
I'D THINK THAT YOU WERE
PUTTING US ON THE OTHER NIGHT

573
00:29:19,991 --> 00:29:21,760
ABOUT BEING ON YOUR SHOW.

574
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:23,161
PUTTING YOU ON?

575
00:29:23,161 --> 00:29:26,030
MR. PRICE, WILL YOU TELL
THESE LOVELY LADIES

576
00:29:26,030 --> 00:29:28,700
THAT I WAS JUST
TALKING ABOUT THEM?

577
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:31,035
YEAH. HE SURE WAS.

578
00:29:32,537 --> 00:29:34,105
HEY.

579
00:29:34,105 --> 00:29:36,875
SO, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

580
00:29:36,875 --> 00:29:38,877
ARE YOU JON PRICE?

581
00:29:38,877 --> 00:29:40,044
YEAH.

582
00:29:40,044 --> 00:29:42,247
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE THE SAME PERSON

583
00:29:42,247 --> 00:29:44,516
I LISTEN TO ON THE RADIO
EVERY NIGHT.

584
00:29:44,516 --> 00:29:46,885
WHY? WHAT DID YOU
EXPECT ME TO BE LIKE?

585
00:29:46,885 --> 00:29:49,988
I THOUGHT YOU'D BE --
I DON'T KNOW.

586
00:29:49,988 --> 00:29:51,723
OLDER.

587
00:29:51,723 --> 00:29:54,392
NOT SO ATTRACTIVE.

588
00:29:54,392 --> 00:29:55,727
IT'S WEIRD.

589
00:29:55,727 --> 00:29:59,931
I LISTEN TO YOUR SHOW
EVERY NIGHT, AND YOUR VOICE --

590
00:29:59,931 --> 00:30:03,802
I KNOW THAT THIS
IS GOING TO SOUND STRANGE,

591
00:30:03,802 --> 00:30:07,005
BUT...IT'S BECOMING
SO FAMILIAR TO ME.

592
00:30:07,005 --> 00:30:09,140
SO COMFORTABLE.

593
00:30:09,140 --> 00:30:10,508
REALLY?

594
00:30:10,508 --> 00:30:13,211
I FEEL LIKE YOUR A FRIEND
WHO'S HOME WITH ME EVERY NIGHT,

595
00:30:13,211 --> 00:30:15,413
KEEPING ME COMPANY.

596
00:30:15,413 --> 00:30:20,351
WHY DON'T YOU COME BACK
WITH ME TO MY PLACE TONIGHT

597
00:30:20,351 --> 00:30:22,353
AND HAVE SOME WINE?

598
00:30:22,353 --> 00:30:24,823
YOU CAN TELL ME
HOW YOU COME UP WITH

599
00:30:24,823 --> 00:30:27,625
ALL THOSE CRAZY THINGS
YOU DO ON THE AIR.

600
00:30:27,625 --> 00:30:31,229
MAYBE YOU CAN EVEN
TUCK ME INTO BED.

601
00:30:37,802 --> 00:30:41,639
AHH, MAN.

602
00:30:41,639 --> 00:30:43,842
I'M KIND OF SEEING
SOMEONE RIGHT NOW.

603
00:30:43,842 --> 00:30:47,045
COME ON. IT'S JUST
A GLASS OF WINE.

604
00:30:47,045 --> 00:30:48,980
ALL WE'LL DO IS TALK.

605
00:30:48,980 --> 00:30:53,451
LOOK, CYNTHIA, I CAN'T.

606
00:30:53,451 --> 00:30:56,588
I'M SORRY,
BUT-BUT I CAN'T.

607
00:30:59,157 --> 00:31:01,292
HERE'S MY NUMBER.

608
00:31:01,292 --> 00:31:05,697
I WANT YOU TO CALL ME
WHEN YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND.

609
00:31:17,141 --> 00:31:20,011
OH...GOD.

610
00:31:21,613 --> 00:31:23,147
[ DIAL TONE ]

611
00:31:26,284 --> 00:31:28,286
[ TELEPHONE DIALING ]

612
00:31:28,286 --> 00:31:30,788
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

613
00:31:32,824 --> 00:31:33,925
HELLO?

614
00:31:33,925 --> 00:31:35,860
Jon. Jon,
did I wake you?

615
00:31:35,860 --> 00:31:37,996
KARLIN,
ARE YOU OKAY?

616
00:31:37,996 --> 00:31:40,031
I COULDN'T SLEEP.

617
00:31:40,031 --> 00:31:42,200
CAN YOU COME OVER?

618
00:31:42,200 --> 00:31:44,702
There's something
I want to talk to you about.

619
00:31:44,702 --> 00:31:46,571
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

620
00:31:46,571 --> 00:31:48,840
JUST COME OVER,
ALL RIGHT?

621
00:31:58,516 --> 00:32:00,451
HELLO?

622
00:32:02,186 --> 00:32:03,254
KARLIN?

623
00:32:03,254 --> 00:32:05,023
Karlin:
JON, COME ON IN.

624
00:32:09,327 --> 00:32:11,462
THIS PLACE IS BEAUTIFUL.

625
00:32:11,462 --> 00:32:14,399
HEY, JON,
THANKS FOR COMING.

626
00:32:14,399 --> 00:32:15,934
YOU WANT A DRINK?

627
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:18,136
SURE YOU DO.
COME ON.

628
00:32:20,071 --> 00:32:24,075
I GOT SOME GREAT
RED WINE HERE.

629
00:32:24,075 --> 00:32:26,244
SO, YOU EVER
MAKE IT WITH CYNTHIA?

630
00:32:26,244 --> 00:32:30,548
HEY, I'M LIVING
WITH SHARON.

631
00:32:30,548 --> 00:32:32,517
SHE WAS SO INTO YOU.

632
00:32:32,517 --> 00:32:36,387
AND YOU CAN HAVE ANY
BEAUTIFUL WOMAN YOU WANT, JON.

633
00:32:36,387 --> 00:32:38,790
YOU'RE BECOMING A CELEBRITY.

634
00:32:40,591 --> 00:32:42,427
YEAH.

635
00:32:42,427 --> 00:32:45,430
SO, WHAT DID YOU
CALL ME HERE FOR?

636
00:32:45,430 --> 00:32:49,300
WELL, YOU KNOW I SAID
ABOUT SOME WILD TIMES UP AHEAD?

637
00:32:49,300 --> 00:32:51,602
WELL, IT CAME TO ME
ABOUT AN HOUR AGO

638
00:32:51,602 --> 00:32:52,770
WHAT WE GOT TO DO.

639
00:32:52,770 --> 00:32:54,238
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

640
00:32:54,238 --> 00:32:55,707
I'M TALKING ABOUT THE SHOW.

641
00:32:55,707 --> 00:32:57,809
WE GOT TO BECOME
MORE OUTRAGEOUS, JON,

642
00:32:57,809 --> 00:33:00,311
OTHERWISE, WE'RE GOING
TO LOSE OUR NUMBERS.

643
00:33:00,311 --> 00:33:02,747
MORE OUTRAGEOUS.
DO YOU THINK THAT'S POSSIBLE?

644
00:33:04,782 --> 00:33:05,883
DRINK UP.

645
00:33:05,883 --> 00:33:07,819
WE'RE GOING TO GO
FOR A RIDE.

646
00:33:09,887 --> 00:33:12,023
I WANT TO SHOW YOU
SOMETHING.

647
00:33:12,023 --> 00:33:14,058
WHAT ARE THOSE?

648
00:33:14,058 --> 00:33:16,361
I DON'T KNOW.
THEY'RE YELLOW.

649
00:33:16,361 --> 00:33:17,795
COME ON.

650
00:33:21,299 --> 00:33:25,603
GRAB THAT DOOR FOR ME,
WILL YOU?

651
00:33:25,603 --> 00:33:27,905
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF THE BLUE ONE?

652
00:33:27,905 --> 00:33:29,040
325I?

653
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:31,609
YOU KNOW IT, HUH?

654
00:33:31,609 --> 00:33:34,612
IT COSTS $50,000.

655
00:33:34,612 --> 00:33:37,448
2.5 LITER IN-LINE
SIX-CYLINDER ENGINE.

656
00:33:37,448 --> 00:33:41,686
DELIVERS 189 HORSEPOWER.
0 TO 60 IN 7 SECONDS.

657
00:33:41,686 --> 00:33:44,489
I EVEN PICKED OUT
MY OWN COLOR.

658
00:33:44,489 --> 00:33:47,191
GIVE ME SAMOA BLUE.

659
00:33:48,626 --> 00:33:51,529
200,000 PEOPLE DOWN THERE
LISTEN TO ME AND YOU

660
00:33:51,529 --> 00:33:54,332
ON THE RADIO EVERY NIGHT.

661
00:33:54,332 --> 00:33:57,235
WE ARE RIGHT ON THE VERGE
OF GETTING WHAT WE WANTED.

662
00:33:57,235 --> 00:33:59,370
I LEARNED A LOT
IN PHOENIX, JON,

663
00:33:59,370 --> 00:34:01,973
AND I'M GOING TO APPLY IT
ALL RIGHT HERE.

664
00:34:01,973 --> 00:34:04,976
WHY DID YOU LEAVE PHOENIX?
YOU WERE DOING WELL THERE.

665
00:34:04,976 --> 00:34:07,412
I HAD OUTGROWN PHOENIX, JON.

666
00:34:07,412 --> 00:34:10,381
JUST LIKE WE'RE GOING
TO OUTGROW LOS ANGELES.

667
00:34:10,381 --> 00:34:12,316
OUTGROW LOS ANGELES?

668
00:34:12,316 --> 00:34:15,586
I'M STARTING TO GET OFFERS
TO SYNDICATE NATIONWIDE.

669
00:34:15,586 --> 00:34:17,388
IF OUR NUMBERS KEEP GROWING,

670
00:34:17,388 --> 00:34:21,826
I'LL BE TAKING OUR SHOW INTO
50 CITIES ACROSS THE COUNTRY.

671
00:34:21,826 --> 00:34:24,128
WE ARE ENTERING A NEW AGE.

672
00:34:24,128 --> 00:34:26,531
OLD TABOOS ARE FALLING AWAY.

673
00:34:26,531 --> 00:34:29,667
PEOPLE ARE NOT AS AFRAID
TO TAP INTO

674
00:34:29,667 --> 00:34:31,769
THE DARK SIDE
OF THEMSELVES.

675
00:34:31,769 --> 00:34:32,804
IN FACT,

676
00:34:32,804 --> 00:34:36,808
THEY ARE FASCINATED
BY DEPRAVITY.

677
00:34:36,808 --> 00:34:39,410
I WANT TO DO
A NEW SEGMENT,

678
00:34:39,410 --> 00:34:42,146
AND CALL IT
"MY BEST CRIME."

679
00:34:42,146 --> 00:34:45,149
PEOPLE CALL US UP
ANONYMOUSLY,

680
00:34:45,149 --> 00:34:48,686
AND THEY TALK ABOUT
A CRIME THEY'VE COMMITTED --

681
00:34:48,686 --> 00:34:51,756
AND WE'RE NOT TALKING
SHOPLIFTING HERE.

682
00:34:51,756 --> 00:34:54,225
I MEAN RAPE, INCEST, MURDER.

683
00:34:54,225 --> 00:34:56,060
ISN'T THAT
A LITTLE HARDCORE?

684
00:34:56,060 --> 00:34:58,096
THE ABSOLUTE CUTTING EDGE.

685
00:34:58,096 --> 00:35:01,165
SURE, WE'LL GET
A LOT OF CRANK CALLS,

686
00:35:01,165 --> 00:35:04,502
BUT WE'LL ALSO GET
A LOT OF REAL CALLS.

687
00:35:04,502 --> 00:35:08,106
JON, THERE'S A WHOLE
CITY OF PERVERSION DOWN THERE,

688
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:09,841
AND WE CAN PLUG INTO IT,

689
00:35:09,841 --> 00:35:12,110
USE OUR 55,000 WATTS
OF POWER

690
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:14,946
TO SPREAD IT
TO EVERY SINGLE CORNER.

691
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,482
I DON'T KNOW, MAN.

692
00:35:17,482 --> 00:35:19,383
IT SOUNDS
WAY OVER THE EDGE.

693
00:35:19,383 --> 00:35:21,786
YOU GOT TO ADMIT
IT SOUNDS CRAZY.

694
00:35:21,786 --> 00:35:23,154
IT'LL BE FASCINATING.

695
00:35:23,154 --> 00:35:25,690
WE'LL HAVE PEOPLE
GLUED TO THEIR RADIOS.

696
00:35:25,690 --> 00:35:28,926
WE'LL HAVE THEM ASKING,
WHO'S GOING TO CALL TONIGHT?

697
00:35:28,926 --> 00:35:31,996
WHAT SICK CONFESSION
WILL I HEAR THIS EVENING?

698
00:35:31,996 --> 00:35:34,866
I BET WE GET A 25 SHARE
OUR FIRST MONTH.

699
00:35:34,866 --> 00:35:36,033
AND FROM THERE,

700
00:35:36,033 --> 00:35:39,137
YOU AND I ARE A SIGNATURE
ON A CONTRACT AWAY

701
00:35:39,137 --> 00:35:41,038
FROM GOING COAST-TO-COAST.

702
00:35:41,038 --> 00:35:43,541
YOU'RE AMAZING.

703
00:35:43,541 --> 00:35:46,177
SOMETIMES.

704
00:35:46,177 --> 00:35:48,079
WHAT DO YOU SAY, JON?

705
00:35:49,380 --> 00:35:51,916
YEAH. HELL, YEAH.
LET'S DO IT.

706
00:35:51,916 --> 00:35:54,452
Man: So, I stole this car
when I was in 11th grade.

707
00:35:54,452 --> 00:35:57,955
And me and a couple of friends
went for a ride to Vegas.

708
00:35:57,955 --> 00:36:00,625
FOLKS, IS THIS
THE BEST WE CAN DO?

709
00:36:00,625 --> 00:36:03,161
Well, hey, the car
was a brand-new Cadillac.

710
00:36:03,161 --> 00:36:04,495
We drove all night --

711
00:36:04,495 --> 00:36:06,564
WHAT A LOSER.
STEALS A CAR.

712
00:36:06,564 --> 00:36:08,633
THAT'S HIS CRIME?
BIG DEAL.

713
00:36:08,633 --> 00:36:11,769
IT HAPPENS 1,000 TIMES A WEEK
IN THIS CITY.

714
00:36:11,769 --> 00:36:14,105
FOLKS, THIS IS
AN OPPORTUNITY

715
00:36:14,105 --> 00:36:17,408
TO GET SOMETHING
REALLY BIG OFF YOUR CHEST.

716
00:36:17,408 --> 00:36:20,645
OKAY, I WANT
TO HEAR ABOUT

717
00:36:20,645 --> 00:36:22,680
